# AirLock – Airpack Platform Architecture
## How .airpac Files Turn One Runtime Into Any Vertical

---

## The Core Idea

The Airlock UI is fixed. The dropdowns are not.

Every dropdown the user sees is loaded dynamically from `.airpac` metadata files at runtime. Swap the pack, swap the entire vertical experience — without touching a single line of application code.

```
.airpac file
    ↓
PromptTemplateRegistry.Load()
    ↓
Dropdowns populate
    ↓
User fills context
    ↓
FillPrompt() assembles the payload
    ↓
Mistral generates the letter
```

The UI is a shell. The `.airpac` is the brain.

---

## What the UI Actually Shows

Looking at the Create Drafts screen, every visible control is driven by `.airpac` metadata:

| UI Control | Loaded From |
|---|---|
| **Letter Type** dropdown | `Title > MainType` (one entry per template) |
| **Letter Sub-Type** dropdown | `Label` field, filtered by selected MainType |
| **Escalation Level** dropdown | Currently hardcoded — future: from `ToneDirectives` keys |
| **Letter Length** dropdown | Currently hardcoded — future: from `LengthOptions` |
| **Context Builder watermark** | `InputScaffold` field |
| **Hidden prompt logic** | `PromptTemplateText`, `RoleInstruction`, `Structure`, `Intent`, `ToneDirectives` |

Change the `.airpac` — the entire UI repopulates with a different vertical.

