## Current .airpac Schema

```json
{
  "Title": "Legal Letters",
  "MainType": "Appeal",
  "SubType": "insurance_claim",
  "Label": "Insurance Claim Appeal",
  "Structure": "Formal business letter with introduction, facts, argument, and requested resolution.",
  "Intent": "Persuade the recipient to reconsider a denied insurance claim.",
  "InputScaffold": "[Who] submitted the claim\n[What] was denied\n[When] the denial occurred\n[Why] the denial should be reconsidered",
  "LengthOptions": [
    { "Label": "Brief", "Words": 150 },
    { "Label": "Medium", "Words": 500 },
    { "Label": "Full", "Words": 1000 }
  ],
  "ToneDirectives": {
    "Professional": "Use a professional and respectful legal tone.",
    "Firm": "Use a firm and assertive legal tone.",
    "Neutral": "Use a calm and objective legal tone."
  },
  "PromptTemplateText": "You are acting as a legal professional.\n\n{Role}\n\nWrite a {Tone} {Length} letter...",
  "RoleInstruction": "You are an experienced legal assistant preparing a formal appeal letter.",
  "_sigil": "owl_440Hz_approved"
}
```

### Field Roles

| Field | Visible to User | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| `Title` | Yes — Letter Type dropdown | Groups templates under a vertical name |
| `MainType` | Yes — Letter Type dropdown | Second half of the `Title > MainType` display |
| `SubType` | No — internal ID | Used to look up the correct template |
| `Label` | Yes — Sub-Type dropdown | Human-readable name for the sub-type |
| `InputScaffold` | Yes — as watermark text | Guides user on what facts to enter |
| `LengthOptions` | Future dropdown | Word count targets per length choice |
| `ToneDirectives` | Future dropdown keys | Maps tone labels to prompt instructions |
| `Structure` | No — injected into prompt | Tells the model how to structure the output |
| `Intent` | No — injected into prompt | Tells the model the purpose of the letter |
| `PromptTemplateText` | No — assembled by FillPrompt() | The full prompt template with placeholders |
| `RoleInstruction` | No — injected into prompt | Sets the model's professional persona |
| `_sigil` | No — validation only | Pack authenticity check on import |

