## What Can Live Inside an Airpack

Airpacks are not limited to what is currently implemented. The schema can grow to support:

**Already implemented:**
- Dropdown population (Title, MainType, SubType/Label)
- Context scaffolding watermark (InputScaffold)
- Hidden prompt logic (PromptTemplateText, RoleInstruction, Structure, Intent)
- Tone directives (ToneDirectives)
- Length options (LengthOptions)

**Natural extensions:**
- Letter header/footer templates (letterhead formatting)
- Jurisdiction-specific language (state/country variants)
- Forbidden phrases list (compliance guardrails)
- Required sections enforcement (must include: date, reference number, etc.)
- Output format hints (bullet points vs prose vs numbered list)
- Domain-specific terminology glossaries
- Escalation sequencing logic (Initial → Reminder → Demand → Final Notice)
- Multiple prompt templates per sub-type (short/long variants)

All of this stays invisible to the user. The pack handles it beneath the surface.

